Uses of Class
lombok.core.LombokNode

  • Packages that use LombokNode 
    Package Description
    lombok.core
    Contains the platform-agnostic core of lombok.
    lombok.core.handlers
    This package contains utility methods and classes shared between javac-specific feature implementations and eclipse-specific feature implementations.
    lombok.eclipse
    Includes the eclipse-specific implementations of the lombok AST and annotation introspection support.
    lombok.javac
    Includes the javac specific implementations of the lombok AST and annotation introspection support.

      class  AST<A extends AST<A,L,N>,L extends LombokNode<A,L,N>,N>
      Lombok wraps the AST produced by a target platform into its own AST system, mostly because both Eclipse and javac do not allow upward traversal (from a method to its owning type, for example).
      class  LombokNode<A extends AST<A,L,N>,L extends LombokNode<A,L,N>,N>
      An instance of this class wraps an Eclipse/javac internal node object.
